      "full_name": "Federal State Budgetary Educational Institution International Children’s Centre “Artek”",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Federal State Budgetary Educational Institution International Children’s Centre “Artek” has been under the control of Russia’s Ministry of Education since the illegal annexation of Crimea and the city of Sevastopol in 2014. Since the beginning of Russia’s war of aggression against Ukraine in 2022, it has been organising camps for children from Ukraine, including from the occupied territories of Kherson, Donetsk, Luhansk and Zaporizhzhia. In those camps, children prepare supportive materials for Russian soldiers participating in the war. In some cases, Ukrainian children have not been allowed to return home and have been pushed to show their support for Russia.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}